{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"12b6edda-6a7f-4b84-86b1-678c6282071e","content":"In your `App.xaml.cs`, override `CreateWindow` and subscribe to the lifecycle events on the returned `Window`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Created\");\n    window.Activated     += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Activated\");\n    window.Deactivated   += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Deactivated\");\n    window.Stopped       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Stopped\");\n    window.Resumed       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Resumed\");\n    window.Destroying    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Destroying\");\n    window.Backgrounding += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Backgrounding\");\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Typical transition order:**\n\n| Action | Events fired |\n|---|---|\n| App launch | `Created → Activated` |\n| User switches away | `Deactivated → Stopped` |\n| User returns | `Resumed → Activated` |\n| App closed | `Deactivated → Stopped → Destroying` |\n| iOS background save | `Backgrounding` (use `e.State` to persist data) |\n\n> `Backgrounding` is **iOS-only**; on Android/Windows it won't fire.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e7fb4d7d-7c17-40c1-80fe-369b62632813","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI Window lifecycle events and how to subscribe to them for debugging/logging purposes. This is a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI development — I can answer it directly without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":426,"requestId":"1120:1FF93E:C01C8F:E09987:69FE85C9"},"id":"abeb9e36-8a88-4621-8f8b-759870181af5","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:54:50.382Z","parentId":"80d28784-5823-4b1c-b534-5cd7e783688c"}
